 =E2=80=98You think Americans are going to come to your aid? Please.=E2=80=
=99=E2=80=9D

Putin has been telling the world exactly
this for a long time: America is not a trustworthy ally. In his rendering, =
Americans are greedy and spoiled cowards who have elections too frequently,=
 and are too wedded to their own comfort, to stick by any missions abroad. =
They may come to your aid initially, but they=E2=80=99ll eventually get bor=
ed and bail out. Not Russia. Putin has been keen to show, by contrast, that=
 he will put actual boots on the ground to defend Russia=E2=80=99s friends =
(never mind the ultimate fate of Syrian President Bashar
al-Assad), which is why he=E2=80=99s been successful in making inroads with=
 traditional U.S. allies around the world, especially in the Middle East.

Ironically, Trump is just amplifying a pattern we saw during the Obama admi=
nistration, when the president failed to enforce his own red line against A=
ssad=E2=80=99s use of chemical weapons in Syria, and again in the administr=
ation of Joe Biden, with his perennial fear of Russian escalation and his m=
icrodosing
military aid to Ukraine. =E2=80=9CNobody believes in Article V anymore,=E2=
=80=9D Bondarev said, referring to the NATO collective-security guarantee t=
hat Trump has repeatedly questioned=E2=80=94including just last week, when =
he said ( https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20250313-nato-s-trump-whisp=
erer-heads-to-white-house-for-tough-talks?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+B=
rightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F13%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Bri=
ghtest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F13%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=
=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) that if alliance members =E2=
=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t pay, I=E2=80=99m not going to defend them.=E2=80=9D Add=
ed Bondarev: =E2=80=9CEveryone knows that the United States
isn=E2=80=99t going to help anyone.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=8A

That=E2=80=99s all from me, friends. I=E2=80=99ll see you back here next we=
ek. Until then, good night, because you know
damn well that tomorrow will be worse.

Julia

